So that the citizens do not relax.
Compliance with the basic rules is strictly monitored.
For example, if a minor is sold cigarettes in a kiosk, then everything will be punished along the chain: the store owner will pay a huge amount, the offender himself will receive blows with sticks on the "back", and the seller will also be whipped and put in prison.
It is thanks to such harsh laws that offenses in Singapore are very rare.
