After the introduction of fines for the year, everything calmed down.
Now the driver, drinking a portion of whiskey, knows: if stopped, the police will not let go for a bribe, impose a fine in the amount of the cost of the apartment and for years sent to prison.
For many foreigners, the city-state in Southeast Asia seems to be a kind of concentration camp.
