“Ten years later,” where adults played adults, has less deep emotional roots, and its parody is more haphazard and includes riffs from stalker films of the 90s like “Hands rocking the cradle.”
In one episode, the character pulls out an Apple Powerbook, four-wheel roller skates, and "a bunch of other stuff from 1991."
