The brothers are fighting for the real estate empire worth more than $ 500 million
The two brothers are fighting for one of Victoria's largest empires in a real estate trade worth more than $500 million - forty years after their Italian ancestors founded the dynasty.
Former director of Carlton Football Club and developer Colin de Lutys lives in the Turac Palace through three doors from his younger brother Paul, who filed a property and asset division lawsuit against him in the Supreme Court.
Paul wants to get out of the family business in 2014, but the Supreme Court continues a fierce dispute about the terms of the divorce.
