Angry residents attacked Solihull's municipality, saying it was "unable to solve this problem".
An anonymous local resident said: “They arrived here on Monday evening, after being driven out of Bentley Heath, where they threw stones at passers-by.”
The municipality should be shamed and forced to act, because they are completely incapable of solving this problem.
The Gypsies were here in May, they were banished, and now they are back again.
More gypsies arrived last night, and perhaps more today.
“The Birmingham municipality knows how to solve this problem, they get long-term court orders to protect their parks,” she added.
I live on Streetsbrook Road and I don’t like the fact that I keep paying municipal tax and the municipality can’t even put an end to it.”
