Italy is toughening its tone towards NGO ships rescuing migrants.
Italy has warned NGOs that own rescue ships in the Mediterranean that they will not be able to continue working unless they comply with the new rules governing their activities.
"If NGOs do not comply with the new code of conduct, it is difficult to say whether they will be able to continue their activities," Interior Minister Mario Minniti said in an interview with the Turin daily Stampa.
