The conflict in the Association of Russian Banks (ARB) is developing: after Sberbank, VTB, VTB-24, Alfa-Bank, Gazprombank, Rosselkhozbank, Binbank and FC Otkritie, seven more credit organizations are going to leave this public organization.
Thus, the share of organizations that have left the ARB will account for at least 80 percent of the market.
But this is not just a way out - all banks that announced a break with the ARB are negotiating with another public organization that unites credit institutions - the Association of Regional Banks "Russia", which is headed by a well-known politician Anatoly Aksakov, Chairman of the State Duma Committee on the Financial Market, recognized, by the way, by the results of the last session and the most effective head of the Duma committee and deputy in the number of draft laws prepared.
The beginning of the conflict within the ARB was laid during the discussion in the Federation Council, when the Interregional Banking Council considered new bills, in particular, suggesting a new classification of banks depending on the size of the authorized capital.
Then Garegin Tosunyan, the president of the ARB, said that, in the opinion of the association, this bill is adopted in the interests of the largest banks, which thus try to limit the capabilities of small and medium-sized banks in the regions, intercepting their clientele.
Among other claims, there was criticism of the Central Bank, which, according to Tosunyan, does not always justify the revocation of licenses from some banks, which, however, was opposed by a representative of the Central Bank: many leaders of the fined banks, in particular, Vneshprombank, were members of the governing bodies of the ARB.
Apparently, this exchange of mutually exclusive views in a very sensitive banking environment to the main regulator and became a visible reason for fifteen major banks, having declared disagreement with the policy of the ARB, began to prepare for joining the Association "Russia", noting that "the effectiveness of the ARB will be low, and constructive dialogue within the banking community is not actually carried out."
Investors will be better.
How will it end?
We will answer the main question that arises at the slightest failure or conflict in the banking sector or next to it: depositors do not threaten anything, rather, on the contrary, the reliability of the banking system will increase.
Anatoly Aksakov, known for his scrupulousness in everything that concerns the interests of banks and their clients, is a high-level professional who is highly valued at the Central Bank: almost all the management of the Central Bank is present at the annual events of the association, and all significant legislative initiatives of the regulator pass through expert assessments of “regionals”.
In terms of personnel and organization, it is obvious that there are also no special shocks.
Undoubtedly, the ARB gets into a difficult financial and managerial situation after losing such powerful and influential participants with their contributions and lobbying opportunities.
However, in this oldest - established in 1991 - the organization defending the interests of the banking community, there is considerable potential to continue to improve banking legislation and the sphere of monetary circulation in general.
It cannot be said that even in the Association “Russia” with open arms are ready to accept new members on any terms, judging by the reaction of its leader, Anatoly Aksakov (“may want too much”), who on July 21 at a briefing in the press center of the Parliamentary newspaper, said that “literally the next day, representatives of banks that have left the ARB asked me to consider the possibility of increasing the potential of our Association “Russia”.
Their proposals are to strengthen the voice of bankers in the Association Council, as well as pay more attention to new banking technologies.
Now the negotiation process is underway, the proposals of both parties are being studied, the agenda of the extraordinary congress of the association is being prepared, which will be held in Sochi in mid-September within the framework of the international banking forum.
That's where we'll decide.
Also Anatoly Aksakov, stressing that "the chair does not hold", called a possible new head of the renewed Association "Russia" Georgy Luntovsky, who leaves in September the post of Deputy Chairman of the Central Bank, highly describing his business and human qualities.
On August 18, Anatoly Aksakov, who is now vacationing in Crimea, plans to interrupt his vacation for one day and arrive in Moscow for an extraordinary meeting of the Council of the Association "Russia", where it is planned to consider the issue of the agenda of the extraordinary congress "Russia".
