Did PSG warn Barcelona about Neymar’s move three years ago?
La Liga member may regret his interest in Marco Verratti
Paris Saint-Germain will not stop chasing Neymar after the club offered 189 million pounds for his ransom, but did they warn Barcelona about the world record raid that took place three years ago?
The sensational offer reinvigorated the summer transfer window as Ligue 1 club was poised to break the world record for transfer cost, more than double the previous mark associated with Paul Pogba's return to Manchester United last season for ?89 million.
When the transition is complete, Neymar will become the most expensive player in the world, as well as the highest paid professional athlete in the world, as PSG offers him a salary of more than 500,000 pounds a week clean.
It is known that Barcelona are furious with how the proposal was made and how Neymar broke the contract, despite the fact that, according to a source close to the leadership of the Catalan club, the club has always done everything possible for the player since his transition from Santos in 2013.
But was the football world warned of this possibility three years ago by the PSG president?
When Manchester City expressed interest in hiring Blaise Matuidi in 2014, Nasser Al-Khelaifi issued a stern warning to any club that would like to lure one of PSG's best players.
“I’m not worried because they know that if they touch one of our players, then we’ll come up against them, we’ll make offers to their players,” Al-Khelaifi said.
“We respect all clubs.
But if they try to recruit one of our players, they will face consequences.”
Barcelona seem to have crossed that line when the Spanish club expressed interest in PSG midfielder Marco Verratti earlier this summer.
PSG has made it clear that it will not release the Italian player on any terms, and now Barcelona is probably feeling the consequences of its offer in the form of the loss of one of its most valuable players, Neymar.
