Two new territories of advanced social and economic development will appear in Russia - Abaz and Novotroitsk.
The relevant decrees of the Government of the Russian Federation will come into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the TOP in the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia are determined.
In the city, where 15 thousand people live, there will be a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investments of residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investment to the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
The list of economic activities in which the special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity will operate in the TOR "Abaza", for example, includes crop production, animal husbandry, production of food products, soft drinks and clothing.
The Government of the Republic has already signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise Abakansky Mine LLC.
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Khakassia fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of the TOP.
The Orenburg region authorities did the same.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk, an area of advanced socio-economic development will also be created.
This will allow diversifying the economy of the monotown, reducing its dependence on the city-forming enterprise Ural Steel JSC, as well as creating more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attracting investments in the amount of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities in which the new TOP will operate a special legal regime for entrepreneurs includes, in particular, freshwater fish farming, the production of feed, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroitsk became the first of the monotowns of the Orenburg region to receive the status of TOP.
The territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investments and improve the life of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of the TOP are the following: income tax in the amount of not more than 5% for the first five years, and not less than 10% for the next 5 years, social contributions in the amount of 7.6% for 10 years, the use of the free customs zone regime, preferential connection to various infrastructure facilities, as well as preferential rental rates.
